🎯 AIM
To install Google Cloud SDK and run a Hello World application using Google App Engine.

✅ STEP 1 — INSTALL GOOGLE CLOUD SDK
Open terminal and run:
curl -O https://dl.google.com/dl/cloudsdk/channels/rapid/downloads/google-cloud-cli-darwin-x86_64.tar.gz

✅ STEP 2 — EXTRACT SDK
tar -xf google-cloud-cli-darwin-x86_64.tar.gz

✅ STEP 3 — INSTALL SDK
./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh
During installation:
* type Y
* press Enter for default .zshrc

✅ STEP 4 — RESTART TERMINAL
Close terminal completely.
Open terminal again.

✅ STEP 5 — CHECK SDK INSTALLATION
gcloud --version
Expected:
Google Cloud SDK 567.0.0

⚠️ IMPORTANT ERROR WE GOT
Python 3.9 incompatibility caused:
gcloud app create crash

✅ STEP 6 — INSTALL PYTHON 3.11
Check Homebrew:
brew --version
Then install Python 3.11:
brew install python@3.11

✅ STEP 7 — SET GCLOUD TO USE PYTHON 3.11
export CLOUDSDK_PYTHON=/opt/homebrew/bin/python3.11

✅ STEP 8 — LOGIN TO GOOGLE CLOUD
gcloud auth login
Browser opens:
* login with Google account
* allow permissions

✅ STEP 9 — CREATE PROJECT
⚠️ IMPORTANT: Project ID:
* lowercase only
* hyphens allowed
* no uppercase
Correct example:
gcloud projects create sonam-cloud-project-123

✅ STEP 10 — SET PROJECT
gcloud config set project sonam-cloud-project-123

⚠️ STEP 11 — APP ENGINE CREATION
Command:
gcloud app create

⚠️ IMPORTANT NOTE
This required:
billing account attached
Without billing: ❌ actual deployment not possible.

✅ ALTERNATIVE WE USED
We continued locally using Flask.
This is enough to understand the workflow.

✅ STEP 12 — CREATE PROJECT FOLDER
mkdir myapp

✅ STEP 13 — ENTER FOLDER
cd myapp

✅ STEP 14 — INSTALL FLASK
pip3 install flask

✅ STEP 15 — CREATE main.py
touch main.py

✅ STEP 16 — OPEN main.py
nano main.py

✅ STEP 17 — PASTE THIS CODE
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return "Hello World from Google App Engine"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='127.0.0.1', port=8080, debug=True)

✅ STEP 18 — SAVE FILE
Inside nano:
* CTRL + O
* Enter
* CTRL + X

✅ STEP 19 — CREATE app.yaml
touch app.yaml

✅ STEP 20 — OPEN app.yaml
nano app.yaml

✅ STEP 21 — ADD THIS CONTENT
runtime: python39

✅ STEP 22 — SAVE FILE
Again:
* CTRL + O
* Enter
* CTRL + X

✅ STEP 23 — RUN APPLICATION
python3 main.py

✅ EXPECTED OUTPUT
Running on http://127.0.0.1:8080

✅ STEP 24 — OPEN IN BROWSER
Open:
http://127.0.0.1:8080
OR run:
open http://127.0.0.1:8080

✅ FINAL OUTPUT
Hello World from Google App Engine

✅ STEP 25 — STOP SERVER
Press:
CTRL + C

